  "text": "Hearts were isolated and perfused as described previously [CITATION_1] . Briefly, isolated hearts were electrically stimulated (DCS, Harvard Instruments) at 300 beats/min by a square wave of twice the threshold voltage of 1.5 ms duration. Hearts were perfused for a total of 50-60 min and functional parameters were determined at 40 min. The left ventricular end-diastolic pressure (LVEDP) changes of isolated hearts were measured.",
